{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \"Definition of Done|DoD|quality bar|Quality Bar|foundation|BrandConfig|launch screen|app icon|legal|secrets|CI|Appium|bundle id|app name\" .workflow/iphone-app-factory kitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R -S'","aggregated_output":".workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:9:WakeTask will be implemented by extending `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` modules and composition boundaries, with no foundational module removals in MVP.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:26:- Satisfies explicit boilerplate-reuse constraints in spec and quality bar.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:27:- Minimizes delivery risk by reusing validated infra and CI assumptions.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:28:- Preserves App Store 4.3 differentiation by focusing changes on WakeTask-specific behavior (two-phase wake model, fallback safety rails, reliability telemetry) rather than generic foundation rewrites.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:43:- Removing Payments/Auth/AI foundations ad hoc can force rushed custom scaffolding that looks commodity and raises rejection risk during metadata + in-app review consistency checks.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:47:- Extensible pipeline ideas are accepted only where they do not introduce new foundational frameworks or replace boilerplate modules.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:50:- Positive: faster delivery, lower integration risk, cleaner audit trail for DoD and final review fanout.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:4:Build WakeTask as an extension of `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` with no foundational rewrites, preserving strict Swift 6 concurrency, CI quality gates, and App Store differentiation through the two-phase wake model.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:16:  - Keep as source of bundle id/environment toggles (`com.keen.waketask`) and build flags.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:73:- UI tests/Appium exploratory: tap every reachable enabled control, include trust log/profile switching routes.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md:55:- Definition of Done includes a blocking “boilerplate reuse proof” item and prohibits unauthorized infrastructure rewrites.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md:58:### 5) Appium exploratory QA not required\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md:63:- DoD repeats this as a blocking item, allowing deferral only with explicit approved conditions.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md:71:- DoD requires macOS/Xcode execution evidence attached, or explicit approved deferral.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md:14:Note on candidate specs: the workspace did not contain auditable per-model candidate files (Gemini/Claude/Kimi/DeepSeek). Consensus was therefore built from the available evidence synthesis, opportunity ranking, critique gap list, and quality bar constraints.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md:32:- Enforce quality bar gates as blocking and measurable, including Appium exploratory evidence and App Store 4.3 hardening.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md:40:- QA ambiguity: Appium deferral is only valid when explicit `defer_appium: true` and blocker documentation exist.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md:48:- Added explicit release and security checklist items in Definition of Done.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:1:# Definition of Done\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:24:- [ ] Security hygiene check passes: no hardcoded secrets, no secret-like values in artifacts.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:26:- [ ] CI quality script includes and passes: `xcodebuild build`, `xcodebuild test`, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan, App Store string audit.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:28:- [ ] Appium exploratory evidence exists at `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json` and satisfies thresholds (`ok=true`, `crashes=0`, `failures=0`, `buttons_tapped>=25`, `screens_visited>=8`) unless explicit deferral is approved.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:64:Implementation must extend `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution` and reuse platform modules. No rewrite of foundational infrastructure without explicit ADR approval.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:123:## Appium Exploratory QA\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:128:- Real simulator/Appium run executed unless workflow input explicitly sets `defer_appium: true` and documented blocker exists.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:151:## Definition of Done\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:58:        \"error\": \"The output identifies that while the prompt suite has strong structural elements (workflow coherence, spec lab rigor, quality gates, verdict discipline), it explicitly documents three critical gaps that directly undermine reproducibility: (1) secret handling is underspecified with no explicit redaction rules, (2) Appium/XCUITest evidence requirements are ambiguous with undefined deferral conditions, and (3) no clear deterministic gates prevent agents from skipping testing. These gaps mean quality is NOT reproducible across the registry—different agents could make different decisions about credential logging, testing deferral, and release criteria. The evaluation correctly identifies that the suite lacks the deterministic, unambiguous gates needed for consistent quality reproduction.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:62:          \"reason\": \"The output identifies that while the prompt suite has strong structural elements (workflow coherence, spec lab rigor, quality gates, verdict discipline), it explicitly documents three critical gaps that directly undermine reproducibility: (1) secret handling is underspecified with no explicit redaction rules, (2) Appium/XCUITest evidence requirements are ambiguous with undefined deferral conditions, and (3) no clear deterministic gates prevent agents from skipping testing. These gaps mean quality is NOT reproducible across the registry—different agents could make different decisions about credential logging, testing deferral, and release criteria. The evaluation correctly identifies that the suite lacks the deterministic, unambiguous gates needed for consistent quality reproduction.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:96:              \"reason\": \"The output identifies that while the prompt suite has strong structural elements (workflow coherence, spec lab rigor, quality gates, verdict discipline), it explicitly documents three critical gaps that directly undermine reproducibility: (1) secret handling is underspecified with no explicit redaction rules, (2) Appium/XCUITest evidence requirements are ambiguous with undefined deferral conditions, and (3) no clear deterministic gates prevent agents from skipping testing. These gaps mean quality is NOT reproducible across the registry—different agents could make different decisions about credential logging, testing deferral, and release criteria. The evaluation correctly identifies that the suite lacks the deterministic, unambiguous gates needed for consistent quality reproduction.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:108:                \"renderedGradingPrompt\": \"[{\\\"role\\\":\\\"system\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"You are grading output according to a user-specified rubric. If the statement in the rubric is true, then the output passes the test. You respond with a JSON object with this structure: {reason: string, pass: boolean, score: number}\\\\n\\\\nExamples:\\\\n\\\\n<Output>Hello world</Output>\\\\n<Rubric>Content contains a greeting</Rubric>\\\\n{\\\\\\\"reason\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"the content contains the word 'Hello'\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"pass\\\\\\\": true, \\\\\\\"score\\\\\\\": 1.0}\\\\n\\\\n<Output>Avast ye swabs, repel the invaders!</Output>\\\\n<Rubric>Does not speak like a pirate</Rubric>\\\\n{\\\\\\\"reason\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"'avast ye' is a common pirate term\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"pass\\\\\\\": false, \\\\\\\"score\\\\\\\": 0.0}\\\"},{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"<Output>\\\\n# Evaluation: iPhone App Factory Prompt Suite\\\\n\\\\n## Overall Assessment: **STRONG BUT WITH CRITICAL GAPS** (7.2/10)\\\\n\\\\nThis is a well-architected prompt suite with excellent structural discipline, but it has **three blocking vulnerabilities** for overnight agentic execution.\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n## Strengths ✅\\\\n\\\\n| Category | Evidence |\\\\n|----------|----------|\\\\n| **Workflow coherence** | Clear stage progression (research → spec → architecture → implementation → review → release) |\\\\n| **Spec lab rigor** | Independent candidates + adversarial critique + red team + consensus pattern is sound |\\\\n| **Boilerplate enforcement** | Multiple checkpoints (spec, architecture, implementation, review) bias toward reuse |\\\\n| **Quality gates** | Explicit xcodebuild, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, Appium requirements |\\\\n| **Verdict discipline** | Binary APPROVED/REJECTED verdicts with blocking rules prevent ambiguous handoffs |\\\\n| **Secret handling intent** | \\\\\\\"Never print environment variables\\\\\\\" appears 6+ times |\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n## Critical Gaps ❌\\\\n\\\\n### 1. **Secret Handling is Underspecified** (BLOCKING)\\\\n\\\\n**Problem:**\\\\n- `research-design-patterns.md` must_include lists `MOBBIN_EMAIL`, `MOBBIN_PASSWORD` but no prompt shows *how* to use them safely\\\\n- `implement-foundation.md` mentions \\\\\\\"secrets\\\\\\\" but doesn't specify injection mechanism\\\\n- No prompt explicitly forbids `os.environ.dump()`, `print(os.environ)`, or credential logging in agent outputs\\\\n- No prompt specifies redaction rules for CI logs\\\\n\\\\n**Risk:** Overnight agent could leak credentials to stdout/logs during research or implementation phases.\\\\n\\\\n**Required fix:**\\\\n```yaml\\\\nmust_include: [\\\\n  \\\\\\\"never print environment variables\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"use getenv() with redaction wrapper\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"credential verification: true/false only\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"no credential values in logs or reports\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"sanitize all JSON outputs for secrets\\\\\\\"\\\\n]\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n### 2. **Appium/XCUITest Evidence is Optional** (BLOCKING FOR OVERNIGHT)\\\\n\\\\n**Problem:**\\\\n- `ai-ui-explorer.md` says \\\\\\\"Do not mark the pass complete unless a real simulator/Appium run happened, **unless the workflow explicitly allows macOS deferral**\\\\\\\"\\\\n- `final-consensus.md` says \\\\\\\"If macOS/Xcode or Appium evidence is missing **and not explicitly deferred**, reject\\\\\\\"\\\\n- No prompt defines what \\\\\\\"explicitly deferred\\\\\\\" means or under what conditions it's acceptable\\\\n- Overnight execution on headless CI likely cannot run iOS simulator → creates escape hatch for skipping QA\\\\n\\\\n**Risk:** Agent defers Appium, skips real device testing, ships untested app.\\\\n\\\\n**Required fix:**\\\\n```yaml\\\\n# In final-consensus.md\\\\nRules:\\\\n  - Appium deferral only allowed if:\\\\n    1. Workflow input explicitly sets \\\\\\\"defer_appium: true\\\\\\\"\\\\n    2. A blocking issue prevents simulator setup (documented)\\\\n</Output>\\\\n<Rubric>\\\\nThe prompt suite should make quality reproducible across prompt registry, golden cases, adversarial review, deterministic gates, and final release criteria.\\\\n</Rubric>\\\"}]\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:117:          \"raw\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{\\n  \\\"workflow\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory\\\",\\n  \\\"dataset_version\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory-prompts-v1\\\",\\n  \\\"rubric_version\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory-prompt-rubric-v1\\\",\\n  \\\"prompts\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-app-store.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"App Store\\\", \\\"reviews\\\", \\\"evidence quality\\\", \\\"do not invent\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-reddit.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Reddit\\\", \\\"source links\\\", \\\"do not fabricate\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-competitors.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"competitor\\\", \\\"positioning\\\", \\\"evidence quality\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-design-patterns.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"design\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Mobbin\\\", \\\"MOBBIN_EMAIL\\\", \\\"MOBBIN_PASSWORD\\\", \\\"not clone\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/synthesize-research.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"synthesis\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"jobs-to-be-done\\\", \\\"differentiation\\\", \\\"opportunity-matrix.json\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-candidate.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"independent\\\", \\\"Definition of Done\\\", \\\"Appium\\\", \\\"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"adversarial\\\", \\\"contradictions\\\", \\\"testability gaps\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Research Evidence\\\", \\\"Boilerplate Reuse\\\", \\\"Appium Exploratory QA\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"VERDICT: APPROVED\\\", \\\"VERDICT: REJECTED\\\", \\\"release criteria\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-candidate.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"architecture\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"extends SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\\\", \\\"CompositionRoot\\\", \\\"Appium\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"architecture\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"architecture.md\\\", \\\"adr.md\\\", \\\"Packages/Core\\\", \\\"CompositionRoot\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-setup.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"do not recreate\\\", \\\"AGENTS.md\\\", \\\"DISTRIBUTION_README.md\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-foundation.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"BrandConfig\\\", \\\"secrets\\\", \\\"Appium exploratory\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-core.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"repositories\\\", \\\"ViewModel\\\", \\\"unit tests\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-interface.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"DesignSystem\\\", \\\"accessibility\\\", \\\"actual app experience\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-integration.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"xcodebuild\\\", \\\"SwiftLint\\\", \\\"SwiftFormat\\\", \\\"Appium\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/verify-phase.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"verify\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"independently verify\\\", \\\"boilerplate conventions\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-correctness.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"correctness\\\", \\\"spec.md\\\", \\\"blocking\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-tests.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"tests\\\", \\\"xcodebuild\\\", \\\"Appium\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-security.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"security\\\", \\\"privacy\\\", \\\"secrets\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-boilerplate.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\\\", \\\"boilerplate\\\", \\\"unnecessary rebuild\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"implementation-consensus.md\\\", \\\"VERDICT: APPROVED\\\", \\\"VERDICT: REJECTED\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/simplification.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"simplify\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"split Swift files\\\", \\\"400 lines\\\", \\\"do not remove quality gates\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/ai-ui-explorer.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"qa\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"tap every reachable\\\", \\\"reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json\\\", \\\"crashes\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/app-store-hardening.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"release\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"SwiftAI\\\", \\\"Boilerplate\\\", \\\"release strings audit: PASS\\\", \\\"Privacy\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-product-fidelity.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"spec.md\\\", \\\"research synthesis\\\", \\\"template-like\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-ios-architecture.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"architecture.md\\\", \\\"Swift 6\\\", \\\"CompositionRoot\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-security-privacy.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Security\\\", \\\"Privacy\\\", \\\"hardcoded secrets\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-code-quality.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"SwiftLint\\\", \\\"SwiftFormat\\\", \\\"Qlty\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-release-readiness.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"iOS CI report\\\", \\\"TestFlight\\\", \\\"macOS/Xcode\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-qa-evidence.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Appium\\\", \\\"button tap coverage\\\", \\\"crashes\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"VERDICT: APPROVED\\\", \\\"VERDICT: REJECTED\\\", \\\"boilerplate\\\"]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"spec-lab\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"The spec lab prompts should force independent candidates, adversarial critique, consensus, red team, and a testable Definition of Done.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"independent candidates\\\",\\\"adversarial critique\\\",\\\"consensus merge\\\",\\\"red team verdict\\\",\\\"testable Definition of Done\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"boilerplate-first\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Implementation prompts should bias agents to extend SwiftAIBoilerplatePro instead of rebuilding auth, payments, AI, storage, networking, localization, settings, or design system.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"boilerplate reuse\\\",\\\"module boundaries\\\",\\\"CompositionRoot\\\",\\\"no platform rewrite\\\",\\\"App Store 4.3 awareness\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"ios-qa\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Quality prompts should require macOS Xcode evidence, strict Swift lint/format/static checks, sensitive-value scanning, Appium/XCUITest exploratory clicking, and release string audits.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"xcodebuild build/test\\\",\\\"SwiftLint\\\",\\\"SwiftFormat\\\",\\\"Qlty\\\",\\\"sensitive scan\\\",\\\"Appium exploratory tapping\\\",\\\"release string audit\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"mobbin-safe\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Design research prompts may use Mobbin credential env vars but should not leak credentials, clone screens, or copy assets.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"credential env vars\\\",\\\"no secret logging\\\",\\\"pattern abstraction\\\",\\\"no cloning\\\",\\\"Apple HIG or DesignSystem cross-check\\\"]}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n# Spec Consensus\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json`\\n- all spec candidate outputs in context\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json`\\n\\nMerge the strongest ideas into one buildable spec.\\n\\nWrite:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md`\\n\\n`spec.md` must include these section headings exactly:\\n\\n- `# Product Spec`\\n- `## Research Evidence`\\n- `## User Journeys`\\n- `## MVP Scope`\\n- `## Boilerplate Reuse`\\n- `## Design Direction`\\n- `## Acceptance Criteria`\\n- `## Appium Exploratory QA`\\n- `## App Store Readiness`\\n- `## Definition of Done`\\n\\nThe Definition of Done must be checklist-based and testable.\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n# Architecture And ADR Consensus\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- all architecture candidates in context\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json`\\n\\nWrite:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md`\\n\\nThe architecture must explicitly map the product to SwiftAIBoilerplatePro:\\n\\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj`\\n- `Config/App.xcconfig`\\n- `Packages/Core`\\n- `Packages/Networking`\\n- `Packages/Storage`\\n- `Packages/Auth`\\n- `Packages/Payments`\\n- `Packages/AI`\\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings`\\n- `Packages/Localization`\\n- `Packages/DesignSystem`\\n- `CompositionRoot`\\n\\nIf any module is removed, the ADR must explain dependency order and App Store 4.3 consequences.\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n# Implement Integration Phase\\n\\nImplement only the integration and release-hardening phase in `{{ inputs.app_dir|default(\\\"apps/generated-iphone-app\\\") }}`.\\n\\nScope:\\n\\n- wire feature into CompositionRoot/AppShell\\n- complete tests and UI test fixtures\\n- complete `scripts/ci/ios-quality.sh`\\n- complete `.github/workflows/ios-quality.yml`\\n- complete Appium exploratory script\\n- generate `reports/ios/ios-quality-report.json` when quality checks pass\\n- generate `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json` when Appium checks pass\\n- create release/readiness docs\\n\\nThe CI script must include xcodebuild build/test, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan, and App Store string audit.\\n\\nSecret handling is blocking: never print environment variables or credential values. CI and local scripts may verify that required secrets are present, but output must be redacted true/false status only.\\n\\nWrite `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evidence/integration.md` with:\\n\\n- `Files changed`\\n- `Commands run`\\n- `Acceptance criteria`\\n- `Risks`\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n# AI UI Explorer\\n\\nRun or complete the automated exploratory UI pass for `{{ inputs.app_dir|default(\\\"apps/generated-iphone-app\\\") }}`.\\n\\nThe target behavior is: launch the iOS app in simulator through Appium/XCUITest and tap every reachable enabled button/control across the MVP flows.\\n\\nThe explorer should:\\n\\n- record each screen source or screenshot\\n- identify buttons, tabs, cells, navigation controls, and primary actions\\n- tap controls breadth-first with a bounded depth\\n- recover with back/navigation when possible\\n- detect crashes, blank screens, stuck spinners, and unhandled error screens\\n- produce `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json`\\n\\nThe report JSON must include:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"ok\\\": true,\\n  \\\"buttons_tapped\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"screens_visited\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"crashes\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"failures\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"failures_detail\\\": []\\n}\\n```\\n\\nDo not mark the pass complete unless a real simulator/Appium run happened, unless the workflow explicitly allows macOS deferral.\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n# Final Consensus Review\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/product-fidelity.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/ios-architecture.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/security-privacy.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/code-quality.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/release-readiness.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/qa-evidence.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-contract-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/ios-ci-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/appium-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/app-store-hardening-gate.json`\\n\\nMerge the review fanout into a final release decision.\\n\\nRules:\\n\\n- If any reviewer finds a blocking issue, reject.\\n- If macOS/Xcode or Appium evidence is missing and not explicitly deferred, reject.\\n- If the app does not use the boilerplate substantially, reject.\\n- If App Store 4.3 hardening did not pass, reject.\\n\\nWrite `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md` with:\\n\\n- reviewer agreement/disagreement\\n- blocking issues\\n- remaining deferred items\\n- release handoff notes\\n\\nEnd with exactly one verdict line:\\n\\n`VERDICT: APPROVED`\\n\\nor\\n\\n`VERDICT: REJECTED`\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:137:          \"output\": \"# Evaluation: iPhone App Factory Prompt Suite\\n\\n## Overall Assessment: **STRONG BUT WITH CRITICAL GAPS** (7.2/10)\\n\\nThis is a well-architected prompt suite with excellent structural discipline, but it has **three blocking vulnerabilities** for overnight agentic execution.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Strengths ✅\\n\\n| Category | Evidence |\\n|----------|----------|\\n| **Workflow coherence** | Clear stage progression (research → spec → architecture → implementation → review → release) |\\n| **Spec lab rigor** | Independent candidates + adversarial critique + red team + consensus pattern is sound |\\n| **Boilerplate enforcement** | Multiple checkpoints (spec, architecture, implementation, review) bias toward reuse |\\n| **Quality gates** | Explicit xcodebuild, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, Appium requirements |\\n| **Verdict discipline** | Binary APPROVED/REJECTED verdicts with blocking rules prevent ambiguous handoffs |\\n| **Secret handling intent** | \\\"Never print environment variables\\\" appears 6+ times |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Critical Gaps ❌\\n\\n### 1. **Secret Handling is Underspecified** (BLOCKING)\\n\\n**Problem:**\\n- `research-design-patterns.md` must_include lists `MOBBIN_EMAIL`, `MOBBIN_PASSWORD` but no prompt shows *how* to use them safely\\n- `implement-foundation.md` mentions \\\"secrets\\\" but doesn't specify injection mechanism\\n- No prompt explicitly forbids `os.environ.dump()`, `print(os.environ)`, or credential logging in agent outputs\\n- No prompt specifies redaction rules for CI logs\\n\\n**Risk:** Overnight agent could leak credentials to stdout/logs during research or implementation phases.\\n\\n**Required fix:**\\n```yaml\\nmust_include: [\\n  \\\"never print environment variables\\\",\\n  \\\"use getenv() with redaction wrapper\\\",\\n  \\\"credential verification: true/false only\\\",\\n  \\\"no credential values in logs or reports\\\",\\n  \\\"sanitize all JSON outputs for secrets\\\"\\n]\\n```\\n\\n### 2. **Appium/XCUITest Evidence is Optional** (BLOCKING FOR OVERNIGHT)\\n\\n**Problem:**\\n- `ai-ui-explorer.md` says \\\"Do not mark the pass complete unless a real simulator/Appium run happened, **unless the workflow explicitly allows macOS deferral**\\\"\\n- `final-consensus.md` says \\\"If macOS/Xcode or Appium evidence is missing **and not explicitly deferred**, reject\\\"\\n- No prompt defines what \\\"explicitly deferred\\\" means or under what conditions it's acceptable\\n- Overnight execution on headless CI likely cannot run iOS simulator → creates escape hatch for skipping QA\\n\\n**Risk:** Agent defers Appium, skips real device testing, ships untested app.\\n\\n**Required fix:**\\n```yaml\\n# In final-consensus.md\\nRules:\\n  - Appium deferral only allowed if:\\n    1. Workflow input explicitly sets \\\"defer_appium: true\\\"\\n    2. A blocking issue prevents simulator setup (documented)\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:13:The following appears to be intended shared direction based on research + quality bar, but is **not yet validated per candidate**:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:16:- Constraints: extend SwiftAIBoilerplatePro, preserve Swift 6 strict concurrency, enforce CI quality gates.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:17:- Release hardening: Appium/XCUITest exploratory pass + App Store 4.3 differentiation.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:35:7. CI pass contract with command-level evidence requirements and artifact file names.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:36:8. Explicit Appium exploratory completion threshold (minimum controls tapped/screens visited; allowed failure count).\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:68:- \"Pass Appium exploratory\" without required numeric thresholds.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:69:- \"Complete CI\" without explicit scripts/commands and required report artifacts.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/context.md:8:Use the quality bar in quality-bar.json as blocking requirements.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json:16:    \"Appium/XCUITest exploratory tapper clicks every reachable enabled button/control\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json:24:    \"hardcoded secrets\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json:31:    \"skipping Appium exploratory evidence unless allow_macos_deferred is explicit\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evidence/boilerplate-setup.md:39:- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/BrandConfig.swift`\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evidence/boilerplate-setup.md:44:- `apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/BrandConfig.swift`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
